<h2>AMENITIES</h2>
<h3>Citadel &mdash; History &amp; Location</h3>
<p>Located in northwestern Calgary, Citadel homes lie within a wheel and spokes layout. The neighborhood is bordered on the north by Stoney Trail and on the south by Country Hills Boulevard. On the east, it is bordered by the Sarcee Trail.</p>
<h4>Homes in Citadel are always in high demand due to the area&rsquo;s unique location.</h4>
<p>Established in 1993, Citadel Real estate can be rightly touted as one of the most desirable and well-designed neighborhoods in NW Calgary. With elaborate walking trails and bike pathways maneuvering around the community and providing easy access to the plethora of play structures, baseball diamonds, soccer fields, skating rinks, tennis courts, Citadel offers a variety of recreational activities for the residents to make the most of their leisurely hours.</p>
<p>There is a central park here with tree-lined pathways. Additionally, you also have an outdoor hockey rink, soccer pitches, baseball diamonds, tennis courts, basketball courts, and a creative playground.</p>
</div>
